   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ARTICLE 19&#x2019;s protection work, based around three strategic pillars, seeks to protect people&#x2019;s ability to exercise their right to freedom of expression : 1. Freedom of expression and vulnerable groups: combating &#x201C;hate speech&#x201D; and censorship targeted at marginalised and disadvantaged groups in a framework that respects fundamental human rights 2. Protection of Civic Space and collective expression: protecting human rights in the context of peaceful protest, assembly and public participation, including protection of civic space, both online and offline 3. Security and impunity: protection of individuals, including journalists, human rights defenders and others who are attacked for speaking out.</narrative>
